article.headline: Sacramento State 88, Eastern Wash. 69
article.story: SACRAMENTO, Calif. (AP) -- Alex Bausley had 15 points, 11 rebounds and six steals to help Sacramento State claim an 88-69 victory over Eastern Washington on Saturday night. The win is the first time the Hornets (11-5, 2-0 Big Sky) won their first two conference games since joining the league in the 1996-97 season. DaShawn Freeman led scoring for Sacramento State with 23 points and Loren Leath added 20. Rodney Stuckey had 21 points and Paul Butorac added 16 for the Eagles (5-10, 0-2 Big Sky). Tied at 18, the Hornets went on a 16-2 run capped off by a basket by Leath to make the score 34-20. Sacramento State led by as many as 23 points and ended the first half ahead 53-32. The Hornets shot 58.8 percent (20-for-34) from the floor in the first half. Sacramento State's defense forced Eastern Washington to turnover the ball 13 times while only committing two to the Eagles. In the second half, Sacramento State increased its lead to 30 points after Freeman completed a three-point play to make the score 74-44 with 12 minutes left. The Eagles never got closer than 19 points.
